{"name": "plinear", "metadata": {"name": "plinear", "version": "0.2.0.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": "https://github.com/Snow0821/plinear", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "torch", "torchvision"], "summary": "parallel neural network layer for binarization of ternarization - quantized layers from the beginning", "upload_time": 1735626911}, "documentation": ["# plinear\n\nGithub for parrallel - linear layer\n\nYou can install PLinear using pip:\n\n```sh\npip install plinear\n```\n\n#### Example usage\n\n```\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom plinear import btnn\n\nclass SimpleNN(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self):\n        super(SimpleNN, self).__init__()\n        self.fc1 = btnn.Linear(28*28, 128)\n        self.fc2 = btnn.Linear(128, 10)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        x = torch.flatten(x, 1)\n        x = self.fc1(x)\n        x = self.fc2(x)\n        return x\n```"], "modules": [{"name": "plinear.models", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "plinear.btnn", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "plinear.btnn.Linear", "xref": {"fqname": "plinear.btnn.linear.Linear", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "plinear.models.vit_example", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "plinear.models.vit_example.PatchEmbedding", "bases": ["nn.Module"], "methods": [{"name": "plinear.models.vit_example.PatchEmbedding.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "img_size", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "patch_size", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "in_channels", "type":